spinning-glacier\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Avoid redundant []rune allocations in UTF-8 truncation\\n\\n## Context\\nPR #444 review comments point out that both `TruncateDescription` and the condensation call site allocate `[]rune` unnecessarily — once to check length, then again inside `TruncateRunes`. This adds overhead especially for the common case where no truncation is needed.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/stringutil/stringutil.go` — `TruncateRunes`\\nAdd a fast path using `utf8.RuneCountInString(s)` before allocating `[]rune`. This fixes the issue at the root so all callers benefit.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TruncateRunes(s string, maxRunes int, suffix string) string {\\n\\tif utf8.RuneCountInString(s) <= maxRunes {\\n\\t\\treturn s\\n\\t}\\n\\trunes := []rune(s)\\n\\tsuffixRunes := []rune(suffix)\\n\\ttruncateAt := maxRunes - len(suffixRunes)\\n\\tif truncateAt < 0 {\\n\\t\\ttruncateAt = 0\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn string(runes[:truncateAt]) + suffix\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/messages.go` — `TruncateDescription`\\nRemove the upfront `[]rune` conversion. Delegate entirely to `TruncateRunes` (which now has the fast path). Handle `maxLen < 3` with `TruncateRunes` using empty suffix.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TruncateDescription(s string, maxLen int) string {\\n\\tif utf8.RuneCountInString(s) <= maxLen {\\n\\t\\treturn s\\n\\t}\\n\\tif maxLen < 3 {\\n\\t\\treturn stringutil.TruncateRunes(s, maxLen, \\\"\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn stringutil.TruncateRunes(s, maxLen, \\\"...\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — no change needed\\nThe call to `stringutil.TruncateRunes(prompt, 500, \\\"...\\\")` already benefits from the fast path added in step 1. No caller-side change required.\\n\\n## Verification\\n```bash\\ngo test -race -run 'TestGenerateContextFromPrompts|TestTruncateDescription|TestTruncateRunes' ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/ .